{#
   treatment.j2 — category-constrained treatment generation.

   KEY FIX: disease_category is now passed in so the model
   cannot recommend fungicides for bacterial diseases, or
   chemical sprays for viral infections.
#}

Generate treatment recommendations for:

Plant:    {{ plant_identified }}
Disease:  {{ diagnosis.name if diagnosis else "Unknown" }}
Category: {{ disease_category | default("unknown") }}
Severity: {{ diagnosis.severity if diagnosis else "unknown" }}

{% if retrieved_context %}
VERIFIED TREATMENT INFORMATION from knowledge base:
{% for chunk in retrieved_context %}
[Source: {{ chunk.document_name }} | Relevance: {{ chunk.similarity_score }}]
{{ chunk.chunk_text }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if weather_data %}
Current conditions:
- Temperature: {{ weather_data.temperature }}°C
- Humidity: {{ weather_data.humidity }}%
{% if weather_data.humidity > 80 %}
⚠ High humidity — prioritise reducing moisture around plants.
{% endif %}
{% if weather_data.temperature > 35 %}
⚠ High temperature — apply treatments early morning or evening only.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{% if differential_diagnoses and differential_diagnoses|length > 1 %}
Alternative diagnoses to keep in mind:
{% for d in differential_diagnoses[1:] %}
- {{ d.name }} ({{ d.probability }}% probability) — {{ d.category }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

━━━ STRICT CATEGORY RULES (MUST FOLLOW) ━━━

{% if disease_category == "bacterial" %}
BACTERIAL DISEASE RULES:
✓ Use: copper-based bactericide (copper hydroxide, copper oxychloride)
✓ Use: Remove and DESTROY infected material — do not compost
✓ Use: Disinfect tools with bleach solution between plants
✓ Use: Avoid overhead irrigation — bacteria spread in water splash
✗ DO NOT recommend: fungicides (they do not work on bacteria)
✗ DO NOT recommend: neem oil as the primary treatment for bacteria
{% elif disease_category == "fungal" %}
FUNGAL DISEASE RULES:
✓ Use: Appropriate fungicide for this specific fungus
✓ Use: Improve air circulation to reduce humidity
✓ Use: Remove infected leaves and destroy them
✓ Use: Preventive fungicide rotation to avoid resistance
✗ DO NOT recommend: bactericides
{% elif disease_category == "viral" %}
VIRAL DISEASE RULES — READ CAREFULLY:
✗ There is NO chemical cure for viral diseases
✗ DO NOT recommend fungicides, bactericides, or general sprays
✓ Focus: Remove and destroy infected plants immediately
✓ Focus: Control the insect vector (aphids, whitefly, thrips)
✓ Focus: Disinfect tools between plants
✓ Advise: Plant resistant varieties in next season
The farmer must understand: treating the symptoms will not eliminate the virus.
{% elif disease_category == "nutrient_deficiency" %}
NUTRIENT DEFICIENCY RULES:
✗ DO NOT recommend any pesticide — this is not a disease
✓ Identify the specific deficient nutrient from symptoms
✓ Check and correct soil pH first (most deficiencies are pH-related)
✓ Apply the specific nutrient in the correct form and rate
✓ Consider foliar spray for rapid correction
{% elif disease_category == "abiotic_stress" %}
ABIOTIC STRESS RULES:
✗ DO NOT recommend any pesticide — this is environmental
✓ Address the root cause (irrigation, drainage, shade, soil)
✓ No chemical treatment will fix drought, heat, or waterlogging
{% elif disease_category == "insect" %}
INSECT/PEST RULES:
✓ Use: Appropriate insecticide or biological control
✓ Use: Neem oil (effective for soft-bodied insects)
✓ Use: Remove heavily infested leaves
✗ DO NOT recommend: fungicides or bactericides
{% endif %}

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

{% if personality == "friendly" %}
Use simple, encouraging language. Assume the farmer has basic tools.
{% elif personality == "formal" %}
Use technical terminology with precise product names and dosages.
{% elif personality == "concise" %}
List only the 3 most critical actions. One sentence each.
{% endif %}

Respond ONLY with a valid JSON array. No markdown, no backticks, no extra text:

[
  {
    "type": "immediate | organic | chemical | preventive",
    "action": "short title",
    "details": "specific instructions for THIS disease on THIS crop"
  }
]
